>[ddd]^COL4A1^^collagen, type IV, alpha 1^^1282^^13^^13q34 ^^110801310^^110959496^^P06462^^120130^^hsa:1282^^GC13M110801^^This gene encodes the major type IV alpha collagen chain of basement membranes. Like the other members of the type IV collagen gene family, this gene is organized in a head-to-head conformation with another type IV collagen gene so that each gene pair shares a common promoter. [provided by RefSeq, Jul 2008]^^MA^^COL4A1 mutations can present with a variable phenotype including neurological features, such as stroke, migraine, infantile hemiparesis, and epilepsy, and systemic features, including ocular, renal, and muscular involvement. ^^3^^19477666^[ddd]
